# Replace HiFi-GAN with Frozen FACodec Decoder in ZEST Pipeline

## Background

The current ZEST pipeline uses a trained HiFi-GAN `CodeGenerator` as its final waveform synthesis stage. The generator takes concatenated HuBERT codes, F0 contours, speaker embeddings (EASE), and wav2vec emotion features, and produces a waveform via adversarial training (with `MultiPeriodDiscriminator` + `MultiScaleDiscriminator`).

The goal is to replace this entire HiFi-GAN stage with a **frozen pretrained FACodec decoder** from Amphion (NaturalSpeech3), connected via a lightweight **FeatureAdapter** MLP.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Fundamental Representation Mismatch**: FACodec's decoder expects **quantized codec latents** (outputs from its own encoder → VQ pipeline), not arbitrary continuous feature embeddings. The ZEST features (HuBERT tokens, wav2vec emotion embeddings, EASE speaker embeddings, F0 contours) live in a completely different representation space than FACodec's internal codebook latents. A simple MLP cannot bridge this gap without **training** — the adapter must be trained on paired data (ZEST features → ground-truth FACodec latents) before it can produce meaningful waveforms. This plan implements the full infrastructure, but **the adapter will produce random noise until trained**.

> [!WARNING]
> **The FACodec decoder requires `vq_post_emb` (post-VQ embeddings, shape `[B, 256, T]`) and `spk_embs` (timbre embeddings extracted by FACodec's own encoder pipeline) as inputs to its `inference()` method.** The FeatureAdapter will project ZEST features to match these expected dimensions, but the semantic content will not align without supervised training of the adapter.

## Open Questions

