## Proposed Changes

### Feature Dimension Analysis

From the existing codebase, the ZEST features arriving at the HiFi-GAN stage are:

| Feature | Source | Dimension | Shape at HiFi-GAN input |
|---------|--------|-----------|------------------------|
| HuBERT codes | `CodeDataset` → embedding lookup | 128-dim (after `UnitEncoder`) | `[B, 128, T_code]` |
| F0 contour | F0 predictor → `F0Encoder` | 128-dim (after encoding) | `[B, 128, T_f0]` |
| EASE speaker embedding | `EASE_embeddings/*.npy` | 128-dim (after EASE classifier) | `[B, 128, T_code]` (broadcast) |
| wav2vec emotion embedding | `wav2vec_feats/*.npy` | 128-dim | `[B, 128, T_code]` (broadcast) |
| **Total concatenated** | | **512-dim** (`model_in_dim` in config) | `[B, 512, T_code]` |

FACodec decoder expects:
- `vq_post_emb`: `[B, 256, T_codec]` — post-quantization embedding
- `spk_embs`: `[B, 256]` — timbre/speaker embedding (global, not time-varying)

